    ]
  },
  "decision": "required_slot_margin_decode_weight stays default-off; margin=6 stays rejected (unchanged from E626). New, concrete, actionable finding: the failure is a position-0 race against the fixed semantic_plan_root* biases, not an unbounded scope leak -- a structural mitigation (run required_slot_margin_bias after semantic_plan_bias in the stack, or exclude frame_depth==0 targets) is now a well-specified next code change rather than a guess.",
  "what_this_is_not": "n=1 (one record, one scratch checkpoint) -- a causal trace, not a quality confirmation; E626's own n=4 numbers remain the quality evidence of record. No checkpoint trained/promoted/synced. No gate touched. Does not validate or replace E626's deferred powered multi-seed margin sweep, which remains open.",
  "next_step": "1) E626's original powered multi-seed rico_held/held-out sweep remains open. 2) Try the two named structural mitigations (reorder the bias stack; or exclude frame_depth==0 from _required_slot_margin_bias's target set) and re-run this same single-record trace to confirm the frame_depth==0 hijack disappears before considering either a real code change. 3) Gallery's 'typed array re-closes empty' regression was not independently traced here and may or may not share this exact mechanism.",
